When an employee receives a job offer, the salary is often stated as CTC (Cost to Company). 
However, the actual "Take-home" salary is lower because the CTC is divided into various components like House Rent Allowance (HRA), 
Provident Fund (PF), Insurance, and other charges.

Your task is to write a program that takes an employee's total CTC as an integer input and calculates the exact value of each component.
Use the following fixed percentages to break down the CTC:

HRA: 20% of the CTC

PF: 10% of the CTC

Insurance: 5% of the CTC

Other Charges: 5% of the CTC

Take-home Salary: The remaining amount (which will be 60% of the CTC)

Note: Assume all calculations will result in whole numbers (you can use integer division or truncate any decimals).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Input Format

A single line containing an integer, ctc, representing the total Cost to Company.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Constraints

1000 <= ctc <= 10^8

The input ctc will always be a multiple of 100, ensuring no decimal points are needed for the percentages.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Output Format

Print the breakdown of the salary exactly in the following format, with each component on a new line:

CTC: [ctc]

HRA: [hra]

PF: [pf]

Insurance: [insurance]

Other Charges: [other_charges]

Take-home Salary: [take_home]
